          "mn28:24.3": {
            "scid": "mn28:24.3",
            "pli": "Vuttaṁ kho panetaṁ bhagavatā kakacūpamovāde “ubhatodaṇḍakena cepi, bhikkhave, kakacena corā ocarakā aṅgamaṅgāni okanteyyuṁ. Tatrāpi yo mano padūseyya, na me so tena sāsanakaro”ti. ",
            "en": "But the Buddha has said in the Advice on the <span class=\"ebt-matched\">Simile of the Saw</span>: “Even if low-down bandits were to sever you limb from limb with a two-handed saw, anyone who had a thought of hate on that account would not be following my instructions.” ",
